### Affected Package
<!-- Can you pin-point one or more @angular/* packages as the source of the bug? -->
This might be related to @angular/elements or ViewEncapsulation in @angular/core

### Is this a regression?

<!-- Did this behavior use to work in the previous version? -->
No

### Description

Any styles or variables set in a [css pseudo-class ":root"
](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:root) within an "angular element" (@angular/elements) stylesheet aren't applied. The root styles would apply on the <html> element in a typical website, but if you're trying to use an angular element to sandbox some structure/style/behavior in an element, if the styles happen to use :root it seems to have nothing to attach to, regardless of ViewEncapsulation setting.


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
<!--
Please create and share minimal reproduction of the issue starting with this template: https://stackblitz.com/fork/angular-issue-repro2
-->
https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-elements-root-css-issue

In this stackblitz I made a custom element called "custom-hello" which is rendered with the <custom-hello> tag in index.html. In the component file, it's setup with the following styles:

`    :root {
      background-color: blue;
    }
    h1 {
      color: red;
    }`

Additionally, there's a css style in styles.css with the following:

`:root {
  background-color: rgb(87, 172, 87);
}`

This ends up showing red text (from h1 css inside angular element) against a green background (from the :root tag in styles.css) but ignores the blue background style rule on :root within the angular element.

Again, regardless of how I configure the angular element, anything I put in a :root style within the element doesn't apply.

